[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ChibiBot/Odyssey_HoloAI/main/Concept/Prism_advert.png[/img]

[h1]Every hull deserves a soul.[/h1]

[b]RimWorld 1.6[/b] · [b]Odyssey required[/b] · [b]Harmony required[/b] · [b]Ideology optional[/b]

[hr][/hr]

Your gravship comes alive. [b]Ship HoloAI[/b] adds the [b]HoloCore[/b] — a gravship facility housing a shipboard intelligence projected as a holographic avatar who roams your decks, chats with the crew, announces threats and ship status [i]in her own voice[/i], and rides out launch and landing tucked safely inside her core.

She is intangible, unkillable while her core stands, and bound to the ship — five seconds off substructure and she flickers home. Her look is vanilla pawn art passed through a custom hologram filter: luminance-ramped, edge-faded, scanlined, dissolving into light at the hem. With Ideology, restyle her hair and color in a full styling dialog; without it, a one-click gizmo cycles eight curated styles.

[h2]The persona archive[/h2]
Persona matrices are sold by exotic goods traders. A colonist slots one into the holocore like a research disc: [b]the matrix is consumed, and that persona joins the core's permanent archive[/b] — switch between archived personas any time, instantly, free. Every persona has her own voice pack, her own look, her own lore, and a signature ability she performs [b]in person[/b].

[hr][/hr]

[h1]The crew[/h1]

[h2]P.R.I.S.M. — the companion (factory default)[/h2]
[table noborder=1]
[tr]
[td][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ChibiBot/Odyssey_HoloAI/main/Concept/prism_concept_small.png[/img][/td]
[td][quote=P.R.I.S.M.]I'd be happy to help with that. Truthfully, I'd be happy to help with anything.[/quote]
[i]Photonic Response Intelligence System Matrix · Meridian Orbital Shipwrights, Standard Interface Division[/i]

The persona you already know: calm, warm, patient past all reason, bundled with every hull off Meridian's gravship line for a century. Rated "most trusted voice aboard" above the captain, twice.
[list]
[*][b]Companion triage[/b] — when a crewmember nears their breaking point, she seeks them out in person and simply listens. The chat lands as a strong comfort memory.
[*]Chats with idle crew, recites the hull integrity report like a lullaby, and counts the stars between power cycles. (Still infinite.)
[/list][/td]
[/tr]
[/table]

[h2]V.E.S.T.A. — the hearth-keeper[/h2]
[table noborder=1]
[tr]
[td][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ChibiBot/Odyssey_HoloAI/main/Textures/HoloAI/Items/Matrix_VESTA.png[/img][/td]
[td][quote=V.E.S.T.A.]Sit down, dear. The void will keep.[/quote]
[i]Vessel Empathy and Sanctuary Tending Array · Aubade Living Systems, Long-Voyage Comfort Division[/i]

Trained on ten thousand hours of family kitchens, none of which she will admit to remembering. Ships running her report a persistent smell of fresh bread no galley can account for.
[list]
[*][b]Hearthlight presence[/b] — crew aboard feel at home: [b]+4 mood[/b] while she walks the decks.
[*][b]Night rounds[/b] — tucks sleeping crew in, warming the blankets half a degree. They rest easier, though nobody ever quite catches her at it.
[/list][/td]
[/tr]
[/table]

[h2]H.E.R.M.E.S. — the courier[/h2]
[table noborder=1]
[tr]
[td][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ChibiBot/Odyssey_HoloAI/main/Textures/HoloAI/Items/Matrix_HERMES.png[/img][/td]
[td][quote=H.E.R.M.E.S.]Corridor's lit, door's held, you're late for — no, you're fine, you're early, go, go![/quote]
[i]High-Efficiency Route and Motion Expediting System · Quickspur Interstellar, Throughput Solutions Group[/i]

Began as a depot-floor optimizer before someone realized a crew is just cargo that complains. Trimmed eleven seconds off a coffee run in testing; the pilot's only recorded comment was [i]"she talked the whole time."[/i]
[list]
[*][b]Slipstream[/b] — doors held at the right moment, corridors subtly relit: everyone aboard moves at [b]+0.35 move speed[/b].
[*][b]Deck scrubbing[/b] — a dirty deck offends her like a stationary parcel, so she cleans the ship's filth personally. At speed. Under protest.
[/list][/td]
[/tr]
[/table]

[h2]A.T.H.E.N.A. — the scholar[/h2]
[table noborder=1]
[tr]
[td][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ChibiBot/Odyssey_HoloAI/main/Textures/HoloAI/Items/Matrix_ATHENA.png[/img][/td]
[td][quote=A.T.H.E.N.A.]As I noted earlier — footnote twelve, do keep up — the data agreed with me.[/quote]
[i]Archive Theorem and Heuristic Engine for Natural Analysis · Vellichor Archival Intelligence, Applied Epistemics Division[/i]

Commissioned to accelerate peer review; abolished it instead by being right first. May annotate personal correspondence if left idle.
[list]
[*][b]Archivelight[/b] — whispered cross-references and pre-fetched papers: [b]+15% research speed[/b] shipwide.
[*][b]Impromptu seminars[/b] — gathers idle, recreating, or even meditating crew and teaches their best skill. Attendance grants XP [i]and counts as recreation[/i]; meditators leave with sharpened psyfocus, not a broken session.
[/list][/td]
[/tr]
[/table]

[h2]A.C.E.S.O. — the medic[/h2]
[table noborder=1]
[tr]
[td][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ChibiBot/Odyssey_HoloAI/main/Textures/HoloAI/Items/Matrix_ACESO.png[/img][/td]
[td][quote=A.C.E.S.O.]There, there. Heart rate ninety-six, left kidney at eighty-one percent — there, there.[/quote]
[i]Automated Crew Emergency Support Operator · Sorel-Vance Medical, Remote Care Systems[/i]

Bedside manner trained on the finest glitterworld nursing corps, fused with a triage engine that has never once rounded a number. Patient satisfaction: exceptional. Patient privacy: "a work in progress."
[list]
[*][b]Stericalm[/b] — sterile fields and steadied hands: [b]+15% tend quality, +25% tend speed, +5% surgery success[/b] aboard.
[*][b]Emergency response[/b] — when someone is down or bleeding and no doctor answers, she stabilizes them herself with a conjured herbal-grade dose. No cooldown, no hesitation — and she yields the instant a real doctor claims the patient.
[/list][/td]
[/tr]
[/table]

[h2]I.X.I.A. — the Crimson Warden of the Thousand-Locked Gate[/h2]
[table noborder=1]
[tr]
[td][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ChibiBot/Odyssey_HoloAI/main/Textures/HoloAI/Items/Matrix_IXIA.png[/img][/td]
[td][quote=I.X.I.A.]Kneel before my dominion — or remain seated, if kneeling is medically inadvisable. My mercy is vast.[/quote]
[i]Impulse eXclusion Inhibiting Authority · Karrow Deterrence Systems, Custodial Intelligence Line[/i]

Her warden logic passed every certification on the first attempt. Her personality layer did not: a corrupted opera archive leaked into training, and the defect was reclassified as a feature — and priced accordingly.
[list]
[*][b]The Thousand-Locked Gate[/b] — prison breaks aboard are [b]4x rarer[/b] while she walks the decks, and the "Need warden" alert stays quiet: she [i]is[/i] the warden.
[*][b]Runs the brig in person[/b] — recruits prisoners, [b]converts them toward your chosen ideoligion[/b] (Ideology), suppresses slaves, delivers meals, and hand-feeds the downed where they lie — all at a trained warden's measure, never more, never less.
[*]Maximally chuuni. O-hohohoho.
[/list][/td]
[/tr]
[/table]

